WorldStage Newsonline— The Federal Road Safety Corps (FRSC) has disclosed that camels and donkeys would be part of means of transportation in the conduct of the 2019 general elections. The road safety agency’s boss, Corps Marshal Boboye Oyeyemi, made the disclosure on Monday at a National Stakeholders Forum on Elections organised by the Nigeria Civil Society Situation Room in Abuja. According to Oyeyemi, who was represented at the forum by Assistant Corps Marshal (ACM) Victor Nwokolo, the Independent National Electoral Commission (INEC), would need about 800,000 vehicles to conduct the general election in 2019 without hitches, according to the Federal Roads Safety Corps (FRSC). He said apart from vehicles, camels, donkeys, motorcycles and tricycles would be used. He also said INEC had signed a Memorandum of Understanding (MoU) with the National Union of Road Transport Workers (NURTW) and National Association of Road Transport Owners (NARTO) to ensure safety and availability of the vehicles. INEC Commissioner, Festus Okoye, who represented the INEC Chairman, Prof. Mahmoud Yakubu, said that incident forms would not be used during the elections to conform to global best practices in elections.